1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, June 30, 2026, as Arthrogryposis Multiplex Congenita (AMC)
3 Awareness Day at the state capitol and to commend Paisley Grace Langton and
4 others who face AMC.
5 WHEREAS, Arthrogryposis multiplex congenita is a condition that causes joints to
6 be stiff and crooked at birth; a newborn with arthrogryposis lacks the normal range of
7 motion in one or more joints; the condition develops prenatally and can be caused by an
8 underlying condition or syndrome; and
9 WHEREAS, AMC is an umbrella diagnosis, meaning it is a part of many other
10 conditions and syndromes, and there are more than four hundred variations of the disease;
11 the most common form of AMC is amyoplasia; and
12 WHEREAS, a newborn must have at least three contracted joints in two separate
13 body areas to be diagnosed with AMC, and the condition occurs in one out of every three
14 thousand births; and
15 WHEREAS, AMC can affect the joints of the hands, feet, hips, knees, elbows,
16 shoulders, wrists, fingers, toes, jaw, and spine, and the symptoms of the disease vary from
17 person to person; and
18 WHEREAS, Paisley Grace Langton is a resident of Sabine Parish who is battling
19 AMC like many other children across the world; though the condition is not curable, patients
